Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a buff-coloured pottery vessel, the exterior, which is now very worn, is covered with a cream-coloured slip and faint traces of at least one line of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (394021) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/394021)
